Sentencas: BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BZY20) proton conductors have been investigated as electrolyte materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characterization of BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ proton-conducting electrolyte material synthesized by pulsed-current activated sintering

Sentencas: The BZY20 powders were synthesized by both a citrate/ethylene-diamine-tetraacetic acid complexing method and a glycine nitrate process, and then sintered by pulsed-current activated sintering.
Titulo: Characterization of BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ proton-conducting electrolyte material synthesized by pulsed-current activated sintering

Sentencas: Densification by pulsed-current activated sintering occurred even at 1300 degrees C within 5 minutes, obtaining a relative density and crystallite size of the sintered body of 95% and 190 nm, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-δ proton-conducting electrolyte material synthesized by pulsed-current activated sintering
